--- Claralw(-at-)aol.com wrote:
> I second that no easy out!!!! 
> 
> I prefer the penetrating oil & banging method
> myself... use a screwdriver or 
> impact driver, and give it a few whacks every day
> for a week, spinkling 
> liquid wrench like holy water (as per Muir).   with
> impact, sometimes to 
> drive it forward, sometimes back.   With buses from
> non rusty areas you 
> generally can remove the screwbolts without this
> extended system, especially 
> the top ones, but often this helps.   A couple times
> I had to torch it.   
> That is why there are some scorch marks on my 61
> from swapping out the 
> drivers door.  
> 
> Since you already drilled to get the door off, I'd
> do the  penetrating oil, 
> and drill through with a small drill bit, then
> slightly larger.  eventually 
> you can peel the remnants of the bolt out.  if
> you're careful, you won't 
> damage the threads. the threads are the same as the
> ubiquitous 13mm nuts on 
> the bus  
